    "where X represents the clean input data, and X′ denotes the noisy input data.",
    "Marginalized Denoising Autoencoder (M-DAE) (Chen et al. 2012) is a specialized version of the Denoising Autoencoder (DAE) designed to handle datasets with missing or incomplete features.",
